bitfield.description: Status to indicate if read on serial VBUS is complete, write of any value will clear this bit.
Write 1 to trigger a read on the serial VBUS
Value written to select the corresponding ECC RAM for control or status
Indicates the number of RAMS serviced by the ECC aggregator

register.description: Reference other documents that contain the ECC RAM wrapper and EDC controller serial vbus register sets. Offset = 410h + (y * 4h); where y = 0h to 7h

EOI Register The EOI register is used to re-trigger the pulse interrupt signal to ensure that any nested interrupt events are serviced. The software interrupt handler must write to the EOI register at the end of the current interrupt processing routine, so that new events can re-trigger the pulse interrupt signal again. For level interrupt signals the EOI register is not functional and must not be used.
